body:
@evilebottnawi 

test repo: https://github.com/Airkro/webpack-resolve-problem

Not work even without any loader. thanks.

In actual use, I didn't use `loader` in the same `module.rule[]`, but added it after the other `module.rule[]`. 

```js
module.exports = {
  module: {
    rules: [
      {
        test: /\.js$/,
        use: [
          {
            loader: "babel-loader",
            ...
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        include: "/path/to/src",
        resolve: {
          alias: {
            "@": "/path/to/src"
          }
        }
      }
    ]
  }
};
```

Otherwise, I have to copy my `loader` option:

```diff
module.exports = {
  module: {
    rules: [
      {
        test: /\.js$/,
+       exclude: "/path/to/src",
        use: [
          {
            loader: "babel-loader",
            ...
          }
        ]
      },
+     {
+       test: /\.js$/,
+       include: "/path/to/src",
+       resolve: ...,
+       use: [
+         {
+           loader: "babel-loader",
+           ...
+         }
+       ]
+     }
    ]
  }
};
```

@Airkro 

> please provide full reproducible test repo and describe what you have and what you expected

I can't understand what you expected
